    Environment Modules

    Lists all modules available to be loaded

    module_avail.Rd

    Lists all modules available to be loaded

    Usage

    module_avail(starts_with = NULL, contains = NULL, ...)

    Arguments

    starts_with

    An optional character scalar. If provided, only modules whose name starts with this character string will be returned.

    contains

    An optional character scalar. This parameter is only supported in Environment Modules 4.3+. If provided, it will filter modules to only those containing this substring.

    ...

    Arguments passed on to get_module_output

    env

    A character vector containing KEY=VALUE entries not as a named vector defining additional environment variables to set

    args

    A character vector defining the module command. You do not need to include the word "module". For example module load zeromq in bash could be converted to run_modulecmd(c("load", "zeromq"))

    Value

    The same format as get_module_output()

    Examples

    module_avail() |> cat()
